Satellite remote sensing
 Cyclone Gabrielle (February 2023)


Sentinel-3 true colour enhance image post cyclone on 21-Feb-2023. Clouded areas are white, highly turbid areas are bright, transition zones are green and the clear open ocean is blue.  This is a companion application to an MPI funded project (SEA2022-12) and report: "Cyclone impacts on fisheries". Specific objectives include hydrodynamic and sediment modelling coupled with observations on the spatial and temporal extent of river stormflow plumes.
